Kotlin Closure
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Definition:
----------------
Closures are functions that capture and retain variables from their surrounding scope, even after that
scope has finished executing.

Purpose:
----------------
They allow functions to access and manipulate variables from their enclosing context.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Why?
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-In java you cannot mutate the values of the variables inside lambdas.

-But in kotlin you can change the values.